# Animation Rules

## Spring Parameters (DO NOT MODIFY without visual testing)

| Animation | Response | Damping | Usage |
|-----------|----------|---------|-------|
| Open notch | 0.42 | 0.8 | Expansion |
| Close notch | 0.45 | 1.0 | Closing |
| Space rail | 0.28 | 0.58 | Active dot movement |
| Badge stack | 0.35 | 0.72 | Badge appear/disappear |
| Hover state | 0.35 | 0.72 | trailingVisibleWidth |

## Rules

- ALWAYS: Spring animations (never linear, never easeIn alone)
- ALWAYS: `.animation()` with explicit `value:` binding
- ALWAYS: `.asymmetric()` transitions for conditional elements
- ALWAYS: Visual test after any animation change

## Transitions

- Badge stack: insertion `.scale(0.6) + .opacity`, removal `.scale(0.8) + .opacity`
- Expanded content: `.opacity` + `.blur(16→0)` + `.offset(y: -10→0)` with 70ms delay

## Performance

- Compositor properties only (opacity, transform, blur)
- No direct width/height animation — use `frame()` with calculated values
- `withAnimation()` for state changes, `.animation()` for value changes

## Anti-patterns

- No `transition: all` equivalent
- No animation without explicit `value:` binding
- Never modify spring params without visual testing
- Never break existing transitions during refactoring
